â€¢ Steps and Commands:

1. We need update:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo apt update -y

2. Then install wget:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo apt install -y wget

3. Then we need to wget the mysql deb files:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo apt install -y wget https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql-apt-config_0.8.15-1_all.deb

4. Install the deb files:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo dpkg -i mysql-apt-config_0.8.15-1_all.deb

5. We need update:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo apt update

6. Then install community server:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo apt install mysql-community-server

7. To enable mysql:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo systemctl enable --now mysql

8. To check the status:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo systemctl status mysql

9. To test if the database server is working fine by creating a test database:
   rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo mysql -u root -p

10. Then start the mysqld service:
    rumpa@rumpa:~$ sudo service mysqld star
